    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHaving something like cmdline or pager open when messages gets sent to the msg output makes them output to (what I assume is) the pager.\n\nIn particular I encountered this for progress events since those are quite spammy.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThere will be easier setups to reproduce this, but these are the ones I encountered. I can try to find a more minimal repro.\n\nIn both cases I had LSP progress set up to be sent to `msg`, and it works perfectly well normally.\n\n```\nlocal max_len = 40\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('LspProgress', {\n  callback = function(ev)\n    local value = ev.data.params.value or {}\n    local msg = value.message or 'done'\n\n    if #msg > max_len then msg = msg:sub(1, max_len - 1) .. '…' end\n\n    local msg_list\n    if msg ~= 'done' then\n      msg_list = { { msg } }\n    else\n      msg_list = { { '' } }\n    end\n\n    -- :h LspProgress\n    vim.api.nvim_echo(msg_list, false, {\n      id = 'lsp.' .. ev.data.params.token,\n      kind = 'progress',\n      source = 'vim.lsp',\n      title = value.title,\n      status = value.kind ~= 'end' and 'running' or 'success',\n      percent = value.percentage,\n    })\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n## Case 1 - Command mode\n\nOpen a file that triggers LSP progress, immediately press `:` to enter command mode.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ce58a31b-4d45-4dc5-a1c4-7ed4b609d0f1\n\n## Case 2 - Swap file\n\nIn this case the second file opened has a swap file and triggers the message when that buffered is open.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/072c952d-b9c1-47cd-a87a-1ab8c9d049b2\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThese should still be presented as \"msg\" rather than spam the pager (especially in the case of progress type updates).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev - commit fd2ea2742536a3bd7711190d94224008d7ca1e84\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo",
