            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "In the progress of trying to find a minimal reproduction I found that it's probably a config error on my part.\n\nI had `'progress'` assigned to `pager`. But it's still a bit funky that  the initial progress message got assigned to msg, and then the later updates just replaces it, unless something like command mode triggers.\n\nBut yeah, as reported this is not a bug. Maybe the \"why does the initial progress message not go to the progress target?\" is a valid issue on its own. I'll make a separate issue for that and close this one.",
